Key Match Events: Andrew Wiggins finished with 24 points, three assists and four steals to lead the Warriors to a 121-113 win.
Desmond Bane had 22 points, 10 assists and two steals for the Grizzlies, but also had eight turnovers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played without Ja Morant and Steph Curry due to injuries.
Others: The Warriors built a double-digit lead in the first two minutes of the first and second quarters, but Memphis fought back each time.
